---
// src/pages/terms.astro
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms of Service for Made @ The Local Pottery and Candle Studio. Understand the conditions and guidelines for using our pottery, candle making, and cafe services."
  keywords="terms of service, terms and conditions, Centerville pottery"
>
  <div class="container py-4">
    <article class="policy-page">
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>

      <p class="last-updated"><strong>Last Updated:</strong> November 2025</p>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          Welcome to Made @ The Local Pottery and Candle Studio. These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of our website, products, and services. By accessing our website or participating in our services, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree to these Terms, please do not use our services.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>1. Service Description</h2>
        <p>
          Made @ The Local Pottery and Candle Studio offers pottery painting, candle making classes, family art experiences, and an integrated cafe in Centerville, Tennessee. Services are provided on an as-available basis.
        </p>
        <p>We reserve the right to modify, suspend, or discontinue services with or without notice.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>2. Booking and Reservations</h2>

        <h3>How to Book</h3>
        <p>You can book our services through:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Our website booking system</li>
          <li>Phone: <a href="tel:(931)729-8459">(931) 729-8459</a></li>
          <li>Email: <a href="mailto:made@thelocalplacetn.com">made@thelocalplacetn.com</a></li>
          <li>Walk-in during business hours</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Reservation Confirmation</h3>
        <p>All reservations must be confirmed before your visit. Confirmation may be provided via email or phone.</p>

        <h3>Payment</h3>
        <p>
          Payment is due upon booking or arrival, depending on the service. We accept various payment methods. Prices listed on our website are subject to change without notice.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>3. Cancellation and Refund Policy</h2>

        <h3>Cancellations</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>More than 24 hours notice:</strong> Full refund of booking fees</li>
          <li><strong>Less than 24 hours notice:</strong> A portion of the booking fee may be retained</li>
          <li><strong>No-show:</strong> The full booking fee will be charged</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Rescheduling</h3>
        <p>
          If you need to reschedule, please contact us as soon as possible. Availability depends on our schedule, and rescheduling is subject to a potential booking fee.
        </p>

        <h3>Refunds</h3>
        <p>
          Refunds will be processed within 5-7 business days of cancellation. Some payment methods may take additional time to reflect the refund.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>4. Health and Safety</h2>

        <h3>Age Requirements</h3>
        <p>
          Most services are suitable for ages 3 and up. Some adult-specific experiences require participants to be 18+. Age restrictions will be noted for each service.
        </p>

        <h3>Parental Supervision</h3>
        <p>
          Children under 12 must be accompanied by a responsible adult at all times. Parents/guardians are responsible for the behavior and safety of their children.
        </p>

        <h3>Health Precautions</h3>
        <p>
          Participants with allergies to paints, waxes, scents, or other materials must inform us before participating. We maintain a clean, safe environment but cannot guarantee allergen-free conditions.
        </p>

        <h3>Accessibility</h3>
        <p>
          Our studio is located upstairs with elevator access. If you require specific accommodations, please notify us in advance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>5. Participant Conduct</h2>
        <p>Participants agree to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Behave respectfully toward staff and other participants</li>
          <li>Follow all safety instructions provided by our staff</li>
          <li>Use materials and equipment only as instructed</li>
          <li>Not engage in disruptive or offensive behavior</li>
          <li>Respect the studio's property</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Prohibited Conduct</h3>
        <p>The following behaviors are strictly prohibited:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Harassment, discrimination, or offensive language</li>
          <li>Intoxication or the use of illegal substances</li>
          <li>Intentional damage to property or materials</li>
          <li>Unauthorized photography or recording of other participants</li>
          <li>Disregard of safety instructions</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          Violations of these conduct expectations may result in immediate removal from the studio without refund.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>6. Liability and Waiver</h2>

        <h3>Assumption of Risk</h3>
        <p>
          Participation in our services involves inherent risks, including but not limited to exposure to paints, waxes, heat, and other materials. By participating, you acknowledge these risks.
        </p>

        <h3>Release of Liability</h3>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, you agree to release, hold harmless, and indemnify Made @ The Local Pottery and Candle Studio, its owners, employees, and agents from any and all claims, damages, or injuries arising from your participation in our services, except in cases of gross negligence or willful misconduct.
        </p>

        <h3>Medical Conditions</h3>
        <p>
          If you have medical conditions that may be affected by our activities (heart conditions, respiratory issues, pregnancy, etc.), please consult with your healthcare provider before participating and notify our staff in advance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>7. Photography and Usage Rights</h2>

        <h3>Personal Use</h3>
        <p>
          You may take photographs of your own creations for personal use. You may share these images on social media with credit to our studio.
        </p>

        <h3>Studio Photography</h3>
        <p>
          We may photograph or record activities at our studio for marketing purposes. By participating, you consent to the use of your image in our marketing materials unless you specifically opt-out in writing.
        </p>

        <h3>Other Participants</h3>
        <p>
          You may not photograph or record other participants without their explicit consent. Respect others' privacy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>8. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          The content of our website, including text, graphics, images, logos, and software, is the property of Made @ The Local Pottery and Candle Studio or its content suppliers and is protected by copyright and other intellectual property laws. You may not reproduce, distribute, or transmit any content without our express written permission.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, Made @ The Local Pottery and Candle Studio shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from your use of our website or services, even if we have been advised of the possibility of such damages.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>10. Indemnification</h2>
        <p>
          You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless Made @ The Local Pottery and Candle Studio from any claims, damages, losses, or expenses (including attorney's fees) arising from your violation of these Terms, your use of our services, or your infringement of any third-party rights.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>11. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms of Service are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Tennessee, without regard to its conflict of law provisions.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>12. Dispute Resolution</h2>

        <h3>Informal Resolution</h3>
        <p>
          If you have a dispute with us, please contact us first at <a href="mailto:made@thelocalplacetn.com">made@thelocalplacetn.com</a> or <a href="tel:(931)729-8459">(931) 729-8459</a> to attempt to resolve the matter informally.
        </p>

        <h3>Small Claims Court</h3>
        <p>
          You agree that any legal proceeding shall be brought exclusively in the small claims court in Williamson County, Tennessee, if applicable, or in the federal or state courts located in Tennessee.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>13. Modifications to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to modify these Terms at any time. Changes will be effective upon posting to our website. Your continued use of our services following any modifications constitutes your acceptance of the updated Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>14. Contact Information</h2>
        <p>
          For questions about these Terms of Service, please contact us:
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Made @ The Local Pottery and Candle Studio</strong><br />
          111 South Public Square, Upstairs<br />
          Centerville, TN 37033<br />
          Phone: <a href="tel:(931)729-8459">(931) 729-8459</a><br />
          Email: <a href="mailto:made@thelocalplacetn.com">made@thelocalplacetn.com</a><br />
          Website: <a href="https://www.thelocalplace.com">https://www.thelocalplace.com</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <div style="margin-top: 3rem; text-align: center;">
        <a href="/" class="cta-button">Back to Home</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  h1 {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .last-updated {
    text-align: center;
    color: #666;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .policy-page {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .policy-section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
  }

  .policy-section:last-of-type {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  h2 {
    color: var(--brown);
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
  }

  h3 {
    color: var(--dark);
    margin-top: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #333;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: #333;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--brown);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  a:hover {
    color: var(--red);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .policy-page {
      padding: 0 1rem;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
